<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<!--
	App Sandbox is intentionally disabled.

	Sandboxed apps can't mount disk images via `hdiutil attach` (the
	system service `diskimagesiod` denies sandbox-originated mount
	requests) and can't write outside their container, which together
	break our in-app updater (download DMG → mount → ditto into
	/Applications → relaunch). We're a non-App-Store, single-user
	utility menu-bar app — sandbox doesn't add meaningful protection
	for what we do (read public IP via HTTPS, render a popover) and
	would block the upgrade UX.

	If we ever need to ship via the App Store, sandbox comes back and
	the in-app updater becomes a privileged helper tool instead.
	-->
</dict>
</plist>
